data.name: Group_Executable.ToolTip
data.value: Enter the name of an executable here. This application must be in the same directory/folder as the executable. When launching AutoBorderless or pressing the Launch button, it will launch the executable, wait for a window to appear, and then attempt to apply borderless to it.

data.name: Group_SearchString.ToolTip
data.value: Enter an executable name or window title here, and either relaunch AutoBorderless or press the "Search" button to apply borderless window to a process that matches either the window title or process name.

data.name: CheckBox_AlwaysShow.ToolTip
data.value: When either an Executable or Search String is entered, AutoBorderless will no longer show this menu and instead attempt to carry out its tasks automatically. Check this box to instead always show this menu. Deleting the INI file or blanking out the terms can also work.

data.name: Label_Info.Text
data.value:
This application can work in one of two ways:
1.) Place this application in the same folder/directory as an executable and enter the name in the "Executable" section. Press the "Launch" button or close it out and relaunch it.
2.) Apply borderless window to an open application using the name of the process (executable name) or window title. Press the "Search" button or close it out and relaunch it.
The first method launches and applies borderless while the second searches for an open process to apply borderless to.
